93 void CTurbSolver::Set_MPI_Solution(CGeometry *geometry, CConfig *config) {
94  unsigned short iVar, iMarker, MarkerS, MarkerR;
95  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, nVertexS, nVertexR, nBufferS_Vector, nBufferR_Vector, nBufferS_Scalar, nBufferR_Scalar;
96  su2double *Buffer_Receive_U = NULL, *Buffer_Send_U = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_muT = NULL, *Buffer_Send_muT = NULL;
97 
98 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
99  int send_to, receive_from;
100  SU2_MPI::Status status;
101 #endif
102 
103  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
104 
105  if ((config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) &&
106  (config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker) > 0)) {
107 
108  MarkerS = iMarker; MarkerR = iMarker+1;
109 
110 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
111  send_to = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(MarkerS)-1;
112  receive_from = abs(config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(MarkerR))-1;
113 #endif
114 
115  nVertexS = geometry->nVertex[MarkerS]; nVertexR = geometry->nVertex[MarkerR];
116  nBufferS_Vector = nVertexS*nVar; nBufferR_Vector = nVertexR*nVar;
117  nBufferS_Scalar = nVertexS; nBufferR_Scalar = nVertexR;
118 
119  /*--- Allocate Receive and send buffers ---*/
120  Buffer_Receive_U = new su2double [nBufferR_Vector];
121  Buffer_Send_U = new su2double[nBufferS_Vector];
122 
123  Buffer_Receive_muT = new su2double [nBufferR_Scalar];
124  Buffer_Send_muT = new su2double[nBufferS_Scalar];
125 
126  /*--- Copy the solution that should be sended ---*/
127  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertexS; iVertex++) {
128  iPoint = geometry->vertex[MarkerS][iVertex]->GetNode();
129  Buffer_Send_muT[iVertex] = node[iPoint]->GetmuT();
130  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
131  Buffer_Send_U[iVar*nVertexS+iVertex] = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(iVar);
132  }
133 
134 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
135 
136  /*--- Send/Receive information using Sendrecv ---*/
137  SU2_MPI::Sendrecv(Buffer_Send_U, nBufferS_Vector, MPI_DOUBLE, send_to, 0,
138  Buffer_Receive_U, nBufferR_Vector, MPI_DOUBLE, receive_from, 0, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
139  SU2_MPI::Sendrecv(Buffer_Send_muT, nBufferS_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, send_to, 1,
140  Buffer_Receive_muT, nBufferR_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, receive_from, 1, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
141 #else
142 
143  /*--- Receive information without MPI ---*/
144  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertexR; iVertex++) {
145  iPoint = geometry->vertex[MarkerR][iVertex]->GetNode();
146  Buffer_Receive_muT[iVertex] = node[iPoint]->GetmuT();
147  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
148  Buffer_Receive_U[iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] = Buffer_Send_U[iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
149  }
150 
151 #endif
152 
153  /*--- Deallocate send buffer ---*/
154  delete [] Buffer_Send_U;
155  delete [] Buffer_Send_muT;
156 
157  /*--- Do the coordinate transformation ---*/
158  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertexR; iVertex++) {
159 
160  /*--- Find point and its type of transformation ---*/
161  iPoint = geometry->vertex[MarkerR][iVertex]->GetNode();
162 
163  /*--- Copy conservative variables. ---*/
164  node[iPoint]->SetmuT(Buffer_Receive_muT[iVertex]);
165  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
166  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(iVar, Buffer_Receive_U[iVar*nVertexR+iVertex]);
167 
168  }
169

254 void CTurbSolver::Set_MPI_Solution_Gradient(CGeometry *geometry, CConfig *config) {
255  unsigned short iVar, iDim, iMarker, iPeriodic_Index, MarkerS, MarkerR;
256  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, nVertexS, nVertexR, nBufferS_Vector, nBufferR_Vector;
257  su2double rotMatrix[3][3], *angles, theta, cosTheta, sinTheta, phi, cosPhi, sinPhi, psi, cosPsi, sinPsi,
258  *Buffer_Receive_Gradient = NULL, *Buffer_Send_Gradient = NULL;
259 
260  su2double **Gradient = new su2double* [nVar];
261  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
262  Gradient[iVar] = new su2double[nDim];
263 
264 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
265  int send_to, receive_from;
266  SU2_MPI::Status status;
267 #endif
268 
269  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
270 
271  if ((config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) &&
272  (config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker) > 0)) {
273 
274  MarkerS = iMarker; MarkerR = iMarker+1;
275 
276 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
277  send_to = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(MarkerS)-1;
278  receive_from = abs(config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(MarkerR))-1;
279 #endif
280 
281  nVertexS = geometry->nVertex[MarkerS]; nVertexR = geometry->nVertex[MarkerR];
282  nBufferS_Vector = nVertexS*nVar*nDim; nBufferR_Vector = nVertexR*nVar*nDim;
283 
284  /*--- Allocate Receive and send buffers ---*/
285  Buffer_Receive_Gradient = new su2double [nBufferR_Vector];
286  Buffer_Send_Gradient = new su2double[nBufferS_Vector];
287 
288  /*--- Copy the solution old that should be sended ---*/
289  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertexS; iVertex++) {
290  iPoint = geometry->vertex[MarkerS][iVertex]->GetNode();
291  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
292  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
293  Buffer_Send_Gradient[iDim*nVar*nVertexS+iVar*nVertexS+iVertex] = node[iPoint]->GetGradient(iVar, iDim);
294  }
295 
296 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
297 
298  /*--- Send/Receive information using Sendrecv ---*/
299  SU2_MPI::Sendrecv(Buffer_Send_Gradient, nBufferS_Vector, MPI_DOUBLE, send_to, 0,
300  Buffer_Receive_Gradient, nBufferR_Vector, MPI_DOUBLE, receive_from, 0, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
301 #else
302 
303  /*--- Receive information without MPI ---*/
304  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertexR; iVertex++) {
305  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
306  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
307  Buffer_Receive_Gradient[iDim*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] = Buffer_Send_Gradient[iDim*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
308  }
309 
310 #endif
311 
312  /*--- Deallocate send buffer ---*/
313  delete [] Buffer_Send_Gradient;
314 
315  /*--- Do the coordinate transformation ---*/
316  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertexR; iVertex++) {
317 
318  /*--- Find point and its type of transformation ---*/
319  iPoint = geometry->vertex[MarkerR][iVertex]->GetNode();
320  iPeriodic_Index = geometry->vertex[MarkerR][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type();
321 
322  /*--- Retrieve the supplied periodic information. ---*/
323  angles = config->GetPeriodicRotation(iPeriodic_Index);
324 
325  /*--- Store angles separately for clarity. ---*/
326  theta = angles[0]; phi = angles[1]; psi = angles[2];
327  cosTheta = cos(theta); cosPhi = cos(phi); cosPsi = cos(psi);
328  sinTheta = sin(theta); sinPhi = sin(phi); sinPsi = sin(psi);
329 
330  /*--- Compute the rotation matrix. Note that the implicit
331  ordering is rotation about the x-axis, y-axis,
332  then z-axis. Note that this is the transpose of the matrix
333  used during the preprocessing stage. ---*/
334  rotMatrix[0][0] = cosPhi*cosPsi; rotMatrix[1][0] = sinTheta*sinPhi*cosPsi - cosTheta*sinPsi; rotMatrix[2][0] = cosTheta*sinPhi*cosPsi + sinTheta*sinPsi;
335  rotMatrix[0][1] = cosPhi*sinPsi; rotMatrix[1][1] = sinTheta*sinPhi*sinPsi + cosTheta*cosPsi; rotMatrix[2][1] = cosTheta*sinPhi*sinPsi - sinTheta*cosPsi;
336  rotMatrix[0][2] = -sinPhi; rotMatrix[1][2] = sinTheta*cosPhi; rotMatrix[2][2] = cosTheta*cosPhi;
337 
338  /*--- Copy conserved variables before performing transformation. ---*/
339  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
340  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
341  Gradient[iVar][iDim] = Buffer_Receive_Gradient[iDim*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
342 
343  /*--- Need to rotate the gradients for all conserved variables. ---*/
344  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
345  if (nDim == 2) {
346  Gradient[iVar][0] = rotMatrix[0][0]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[0*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[0][1]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[1*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
347  Gradient[iVar][1] = rotMatrix[1][0]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[0*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[1][1]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[1*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
348  }
349  else {
350  Gradient[iVar][0] = rotMatrix[0][0]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[0*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[0][1]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[1*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[0][2]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[2*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
351  Gradient[iVar][1] = rotMatrix[1][0]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[0*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[1][1]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[1*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[1][2]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[2*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
352  Gradient[iVar][2] = rotMatrix[2][0]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[0*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[2][1]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[1*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex] + rotMatrix[2][2]*Buffer_Receive_Gradient[2*nVar*nVertexR+iVar*nVertexR+iVertex];
353  }
354  }
355 
356  /*--- Store the received information ---*/
357  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
358  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
359  node[iPoint]->SetGradient(iVar, iDim, Gradient[iVar][iDim]);
360 
361  }
362 
363  /*--- Deallocate receive buffer ---*/
364  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Gradient;
365 
366  }
367 
368  }
369 
370  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
371  delete [] Gradient[iVar];
372  delete [] Gradient;
373

456 void CTurbSolver::Upwind_Residual(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh) {
457 
458  su2double *Turb_i, *Turb_j, *Limiter_i = NULL, *Limiter_j = NULL, *V_i, *V_j, **Gradient_i, **Gradient_j, Project_Grad_i, Project_Grad_j;
459  unsigned long iEdge, iPoint, jPoint;
460  unsigned short iDim, iVar;
461 
462  bool muscl = config->GetMUSCL_Turb();
463  bool limiter = (config->GetKind_SlopeLimit_Turb() != NO_LIMITER);
464  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
465 
466  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
467 
468  /*--- Points in edge and normal vectors ---*/
469 
470  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0);
471  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1);
472  numerics->SetNormal(geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNormal());
473 
474  /*--- Primitive variables w/o reconstruction ---*/
475 
476  V_i = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
477  V_j = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetPrimitive();
478  numerics->SetPrimitive(V_i, V_j);
479 
480  /*--- Turbulent variables w/o reconstruction ---*/
481 
482  Turb_i = node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
483  Turb_j = node[jPoint]->GetSolution();
484  numerics->SetTurbVar(Turb_i, Turb_j);
485 
486  /*--- Grid Movement ---*/
487 
488  if (grid_movement)
489  numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel(), geometry->node[jPoint]->GetGridVel());
490 
491  if (muscl) {
492 
493  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
494  Vector_i[iDim] = 0.5*(geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord(iDim) - geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(iDim));
495  Vector_j[iDim] = 0.5*(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(iDim) - geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord(iDim));
496  }
497 
498  /*--- Mean flow primitive variables using gradient reconstruction and limiters ---*/
499 
500  Gradient_i = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive();
501  Gradient_j = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive();
502  if (limiter) {
503  Limiter_i = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetLimiter_Primitive();
504  Limiter_j = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetLimiter_Primitive();
505  }
506 
507  for (iVar = 0; iVar < solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->GetnPrimVarGrad(); iVar++) {
508  Project_Grad_i = 0.0; Project_Grad_j = 0.0;
509  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
510  Project_Grad_i += Vector_i[iDim]*Gradient_i[iVar][iDim];
511  Project_Grad_j += Vector_j[iDim]*Gradient_j[iVar][iDim];
512  }
513  if (limiter) {
514  FlowPrimVar_i[iVar] = V_i[iVar] + Limiter_i[iVar]*Project_Grad_i;
515  FlowPrimVar_j[iVar] = V_j[iVar] + Limiter_j[iVar]*Project_Grad_j;
516  }
517  else {
518  FlowPrimVar_i[iVar] = V_i[iVar] + Project_Grad_i;
519  FlowPrimVar_j[iVar] = V_j[iVar] + Project_Grad_j;
520  }
521  }
522 
523  numerics->SetPrimitive(FlowPrimVar_i, FlowPrimVar_j);
524 
525  /*--- Turbulent variables using gradient reconstruction and limiters ---*/
526 
527  Gradient_i = node[iPoint]->GetGradient();
528  Gradient_j = node[jPoint]->GetGradient();
529  if (limiter) {
530  Limiter_i = node[iPoint]->GetLimiter();
531  Limiter_j = node[jPoint]->GetLimiter();
532  }
533 
534  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
535  Project_Grad_i = 0.0; Project_Grad_j = 0.0;
536  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
537  Project_Grad_i += Vector_i[iDim]*Gradient_i[iVar][iDim];
538  Project_Grad_j += Vector_j[iDim]*Gradient_j[iVar][iDim];
539  }
540  if (limiter) {
541  Solution_i[iVar] = Turb_i[iVar] + Limiter_i[iVar]*Project_Grad_i;
542  Solution_j[iVar] = Turb_j[iVar] + Limiter_j[iVar]*Project_Grad_j;
543  }
544  else {
545  Solution_i[iVar] = Turb_i[iVar] + Project_Grad_i;
546  Solution_j[iVar] = Turb_j[iVar] + Project_Grad_j;
547  }
548  }
549 
550  numerics->SetTurbVar(Solution_i, Solution_j);
551 
552  }
553 
554  /*--- Add and subtract residual ---*/
555 
556  numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
557 
558  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
559  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(jPoint, Residual);
560 
561  /*--- Implicit part ---*/
562 
563  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
564  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, jPoint, Jacobian_j);
565  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(jPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
566  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(jPoint, jPoint, Jacobian_j);
567 
568  }
569

572 void CTurbSolver::Viscous_Residual(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *numerics,
573  CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh, unsigned short iRKStep) {
574  unsigned long iEdge, iPoint, jPoint;
575 
576  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
577 
578  /*--- Points in edge ---*/
579 
580  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0);
581  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1);
582 
583  /*--- Points coordinates, and normal vector ---*/
584 
585  numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(),
586  geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord());
587  numerics->SetNormal(geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNormal());
588 
589  /*--- Conservative variables w/o reconstruction ---*/
590 
591  numerics->SetPrimitive(solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive(),
592  solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetPrimitive());
593 
594  /*--- Turbulent variables w/o reconstruction, and its gradients ---*/
595 
596  numerics->SetTurbVar(node[iPoint]->GetSolution(), node[jPoint]->GetSolution());
597  numerics->SetTurbVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient(), node[jPoint]->GetGradient());
598 
599  /*--- Menter's first blending function (only SST)---*/
600  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
601  numerics->SetF1blending(node[iPoint]->GetF1blending(), node[jPoint]->GetF1blending());
602 
603  /*--- Compute residual, and Jacobians ---*/
604 
605  numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
606 
607  /*--- Add and subtract residual, and update Jacobians ---*/
608 
609  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
610  LinSysRes.AddBlock(jPoint, Residual);
611 
612  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
613  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, jPoint, Jacobian_j);
614  Jacobian.AddBlock(jPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
615  Jacobian.AddBlock(jPoint, jPoint, Jacobian_j);
616 
617  }
618 
619 }

689 void CTurbSolver::ImplicitEuler_Iteration(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config) {
690 
691  unsigned short iVar;
692  unsigned long iPoint, total_index;
693  su2double Delta, Vol, density_old = 0.0, density = 0.0;
694 
695  bool adjoint = config->GetContinuous_Adjoint() || (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint() && config->GetFrozen_Visc_Disc());
696  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
697  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
698 
699  /*--- Set maximum residual to zero ---*/
700 
701  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
702  SetRes_RMS(iVar, 0.0);
703  SetRes_Max(iVar, 0.0, 0);
704  }
705 
706  /*--- Build implicit system ---*/
707 
708  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
709 
710  /*--- Read the volume ---*/
711 
712  Vol = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
713 
714  /*--- Modify matrix diagonal to assure diagonal dominance ---*/
715 
716  Delta = Vol / (config->GetCFLRedCoeff_Turb()*solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDelta_Time());
717  Jacobian.AddVal2Diag(iPoint, Delta);
718 
719  /*--- Right hand side of the system (-Residual) and initial guess (x = 0) ---*/
720 
721  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
722  total_index = iPoint*nVar+iVar;
723  LinSysRes[total_index] = - LinSysRes[total_index];
724  LinSysSol[total_index] = 0.0;
725  AddRes_RMS(iVar, LinSysRes[total_index]*LinSysRes[total_index]);
726  AddRes_Max(iVar, fabs(LinSysRes[total_index]), geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex(), geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord());
727  }
728  }
729 
730  /*--- Initialize residual and solution at the ghost points ---*/
731 
732  for (iPoint = nPointDomain; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++) {
733  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
734  total_index = iPoint*nVar + iVar;
735  LinSysRes[total_index] = 0.0;
736  LinSysSol[total_index] = 0.0;
737  }
738  }
739 
740  /*--- Solve or smooth the linear system ---*/
741 
742  CSysSolve system;
743  system.Solve(Jacobian, LinSysRes, LinSysSol, geometry, config);
744 
745  /*--- Update solution (system written in terms of increments) ---*/
746 
747  if (!adjoint) {
748 
749  /*--- Update and clip trubulent solution ---*/
750 
751  switch (config->GetKind_Turb_Model()) {
752 
753  case SA: case SA_E: case SA_COMP: case SA_E_COMP:
754 
755  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
756  node[iPoint]->AddClippedSolution(0, config->GetRelaxation_Factor_Turb()*LinSysSol[iPoint], lowerlimit[0], upperlimit[0]);
757  }
758 
759  break;
760 
761  case SA_NEG:
762 
763  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
764  node[iPoint]->AddSolution(0, config->GetRelaxation_Factor_Turb()*LinSysSol[iPoint]);
765  }
766 
767  break;
768 
769  case SST:
770 
771  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
772 
773  if (compressible) {
774  density_old = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_Old(0);
775  density = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
776  }
777  if (incompressible) {
778  density_old = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity_Old();
779  density = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
780  }
781 
782  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
783  node[iPoint]->AddConservativeSolution(iVar, config->GetRelaxation_Factor_Turb()*LinSysSol[iPoint*nVar+iVar], density, density_old, lowerlimit[iVar], upperlimit[iVar]);
784  }
785 
786  }
787 
788  break;
789 
790  }
791  }
792 
793 
794  /*--- MPI solution ---*/
795 
796  Set_MPI_Solution(geometry, config);
797 
798  /*--- Compute the root mean square residual ---*/
799 
800  SetResidual_RMS(geometry, config);
801 
802 }
803 
804 void CTurbSolver::SetResidual_DualTime(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config,
805  unsigned short iRKStep, unsigned short iMesh, unsigned short RunTime_EqSystem) {
806 
807  /*--- Local variables ---*/
808 
809  unsigned short iVar, jVar, iMarker, iDim;
810  unsigned long iPoint, jPoint, iEdge, iVertex;
811 
812  su2double *U_time_nM1, *U_time_n, *U_time_nP1;
813  su2double Volume_nM1, Volume_nP1, TimeStep;
814  su2double Density_nM1, Density_n, Density_nP1;
815  su2double *Normal = NULL, *GridVel_i = NULL, *GridVel_j = NULL, Residual_GCL;
816 
817  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Turb() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
818  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
819 
820  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
821 
822  /*--- Store the physical time step ---*/
823 
824  TimeStep = config->GetDelta_UnstTimeND();
825 
826  /*--- Compute the dual time-stepping source term for static meshes ---*/
827 
828  if (!grid_movement) {
829 
830  /*--- Loop over all nodes (excluding halos) ---*/
831 
832  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
833 
834  /*--- Retrieve the solution at time levels n-1, n, and n+1. Note that
835  we are currently iterating on U^n+1 and that U^n & U^n-1 are fixed,
836  previous solutions that are stored in memory. ---*/
837 
838  U_time_nM1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n1();
839  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
840  U_time_nP1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
841 
842  /*--- CV volume at time n+1. As we are on a static mesh, the volume
843  of the CV will remained fixed for all time steps. ---*/
844 
845  Volume_nP1 = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
846 
847  /*--- Compute the dual time-stepping source term based on the chosen
848  time discretization scheme (1st- or 2nd-order).---*/
849 
850  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST) {
851 
852  /*--- If this is the SST model, we need to multiply by the density
853  in order to get the conservative variables ---*/
854  if (incompressible){
855  /*--- This is temporary and only valid for constant-density problems:
856  density could also be temperature dependent, but as it is not a part
857  of the solution vector it's neither stored for previous time steps
858  nor updated with the solution at the end of each iteration. */
859  Density_nM1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
860  Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
861  Density_nP1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
862  }
863  else{
864  Density_nM1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n1()[0];
865  Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n()[0];
866  Density_nP1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution()[0];
867  }
868 
869  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
870  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
871  Residual[iVar] = ( Density_nP1*U_time_nP1[iVar] - Density_n*U_time_n[iVar])*Volume_nP1 / TimeStep;
872  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
873  Residual[iVar] = ( 3.0*Density_nP1*U_time_nP1[iVar] - 4.0*Density_n*U_time_n[iVar]
874  +1.0*Density_nM1*U_time_nM1[iVar])*Volume_nP1 / (2.0*TimeStep);
875  }
876 
877  } else {
878 
879  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
880  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
881  Residual[iVar] = (U_time_nP1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*Volume_nP1 / TimeStep;
882  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
883  Residual[iVar] = ( 3.0*U_time_nP1[iVar] - 4.0*U_time_n[iVar]
884  +1.0*U_time_nM1[iVar])*Volume_nP1 / (2.0*TimeStep);
885  }
886  }
887 
888  /*--- Store the residual and compute the Jacobian contribution due
889  to the dual time source term. ---*/
890 
891  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
892  if (implicit) {
893  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
894  for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
895  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
896  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = Volume_nP1 / TimeStep;
897  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
898  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = (Volume_nP1*3.0)/(2.0*TimeStep);
899  }
900  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
901  }
902  }
903 
904  } else {
905 
906  /*--- For unsteady flows on dynamic meshes (rigidly transforming or
907  dynamically deforming), the Geometric Conservation Law (GCL) should be
908  satisfied in conjunction with the ALE formulation of the governing
909  equations. The GCL prevents accuracy issues caused by grid motion, i.e.
910  a uniform free-stream should be preserved through a moving grid. First,
911  we will loop over the edges and boundaries to compute the GCL component
912  of the dual time source term that depends on grid velocities. ---*/
913 
914  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
915 
916  /*--- Get indices for nodes i & j plus the face normal ---*/
917 
918  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0);
919  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1);
920  Normal = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNormal();
921 
922  /*--- Grid velocities stored at nodes i & j ---*/
923 
924  GridVel_i = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
925  GridVel_j = geometry->node[jPoint]->GetGridVel();
926 
927  /*--- Compute the GCL term by averaging the grid velocities at the
928  edge mid-point and dotting with the face normal. ---*/
929 
930  Residual_GCL = 0.0;
931  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
932  Residual_GCL += 0.5*(GridVel_i[iDim]+GridVel_j[iDim])*Normal[iDim];
933 
934  /*--- Compute the GCL component of the source term for node i ---*/
935 
936  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
937 
938  /*--- Multiply by density at node i for the SST model ---*/
939 
940  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST) {
941  if (incompressible) Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity(); // Temporary fix
942  else Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n()[0];
943  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
944  Residual[iVar] = Density_n*U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
945  } else {
946  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
947  Residual[iVar] = U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
948  }
949  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
950 
951  /*--- Compute the GCL component of the source term for node j ---*/
952 
953  U_time_n = node[jPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
954 
955  /*--- Multiply by density at node j for the SST model ---*/
956 
957  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST) {
958  if (incompressible) Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetDensity(); // Temporary fix
959  else Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetSolution_time_n()[0];
960  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
961  Residual[iVar] = Density_n*U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
962  } else {
963  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
964  Residual[iVar] = U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
965  }
966  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(jPoint, Residual);
967 
968  }
969 
970  /*--- Loop over the boundary edges ---*/
971 
972  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < geometry->GetnMarker(); iMarker++) {
973  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) != INTERNAL_BOUNDARY)
974  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->GetnVertex(iMarker); iVertex++) {
975 
976  /*--- Get the index for node i plus the boundary face normal ---*/
977 
978  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
979  Normal = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal();
980 
981  /*--- Grid velocities stored at boundary node i ---*/
982 
983  GridVel_i = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
984 
985  /*--- Compute the GCL term by dotting the grid velocity with the face
986  normal. The normal is negated to match the boundary convention. ---*/
987 
988  Residual_GCL = 0.0;
989  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
990  Residual_GCL -= 0.5*(GridVel_i[iDim]+GridVel_i[iDim])*Normal[iDim];
991 
992  /*--- Compute the GCL component of the source term for node i ---*/
993 
994  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
995 
996  /*--- Multiply by density at node i for the SST model ---*/
997 
998  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST) {
999  if (incompressible) Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity(); // Temporary fix
1000  else Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n()[0];
1001  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
1002  Residual[iVar] = Density_n*U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
1003  } else {
1004  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
1005  Residual[iVar] = U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
1006  }
1007  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
1008  }
1009  }
1010 
1011  /*--- Loop over all nodes (excluding halos) to compute the remainder
1012  of the dual time-stepping source term. ---*/
1013 
1014  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
1015 
1016  /*--- Retrieve the solution at time levels n-1, n, and n+1. Note that
1017  we are currently iterating on U^n+1 and that U^n & U^n-1 are fixed,
1018  previous solutions that are stored in memory. ---*/
1019 
1020  U_time_nM1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n1();
1021  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
1022  U_time_nP1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
1023 
1024  /*--- CV volume at time n-1 and n+1. In the case of dynamically deforming
1025  grids, the volumes will change. On rigidly transforming grids, the
1026  volumes will remain constant. ---*/
1027 
1028  Volume_nM1 = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume_nM1();
1029  Volume_nP1 = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
1030 
1031  /*--- Compute the dual time-stepping source residual. Due to the
1032  introduction of the GCL term above, the remainder of the source residual
1033  due to the time discretization has a new form.---*/
1034 
1035  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST) {
1036 
1037  /*--- If this is the SST model, we need to multiply by the density
1038  in order to get the conservative variables ---*/
1039  if (incompressible){
1040  /*--- This is temporary and only valid for constant-density problems:
1041  density could also be temperature dependent, but as it is not a part
1042  of the solution vector it's neither stored for previous time steps
1043  nor updated with the solution at the end of each iteration. */
1044  Density_nM1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
1045  Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
1046  Density_nP1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
1047  }
1048  else{
1049  Density_nM1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n1()[0];
1050  Density_n = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n()[0];
1051  Density_nP1 = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution()[0];
1052  }
1053 
1054  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1055  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
1056  Residual[iVar] = (Density_nP1*U_time_nP1[iVar] - Density_n*U_time_n[iVar])*(Volume_nP1/TimeStep);
1057  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
1058  Residual[iVar] = (Density_nP1*U_time_nP1[iVar] - Density_n*U_time_n[iVar])*(3.0*Volume_nP1/(2.0*TimeStep))
1059  + (Density_nM1*U_time_nM1[iVar] - Density_n*U_time_n[iVar])*(Volume_nM1/(2.0*TimeStep));
1060  }
1061 
1062  } else {
1063 
1064  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1065  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
1066  Residual[iVar] = (U_time_nP1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*(Volume_nP1/TimeStep);
1067  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
1068  Residual[iVar] = (U_time_nP1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*(3.0*Volume_nP1/(2.0*TimeStep))
1069  + (U_time_nM1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*(Volume_nM1/(2.0*TimeStep));
1070  }
1071  }
1072 
1073  /*--- Store the residual and compute the Jacobian contribution due
1074  to the dual time source term. ---*/
1075 
1076  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
1077  if (implicit) {
1078  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1079  for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
1080  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
1081  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = Volume_nP1/TimeStep;
1082  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
1083  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = (3.0*Volume_nP1)/(2.0*TimeStep);
1084  }
1085  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
1086  }
1087  }
1088  }

1093 void CTurbSolver::LoadRestart(CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CConfig *config, int val_iter, bool val_update_geo) {
1094 
1095  /*--- Restart the solution from file information ---*/
1096 
1097  unsigned short iVar, iMesh;
1098  unsigned long iPoint, index, iChildren, Point_Fine;
1099  su2double Area_Children, Area_Parent, *Solution_Fine;
1100  bool dual_time = ((config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
1101  (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND));
1102  bool time_stepping = (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == TIME_STEPPING);
1103  unsigned short iZone = config->GetiZone();
1104  unsigned short nZone = config->GetnZone();
1105 
1106  string UnstExt, text_line;
1107  ifstream restart_file;
1108  string restart_filename = config->GetSolution_FlowFileName();
1109 
1110  /*--- Modify file name for multizone problems ---*/
1111  if (nZone >1)
1112  restart_filename = config->GetMultizone_FileName(restart_filename, iZone);
1113 
1114  /*--- Modify file name for an unsteady restart ---*/
1115 
1116  if (dual_time|| time_stepping)
1117  restart_filename = config->GetUnsteady_FileName(restart_filename, val_iter);
1118 
1119  /*--- Read the restart data from either an ASCII or binary SU2 file. ---*/
1120 
1121  if (config->GetRead_Binary_Restart()) {
1122  Read_SU2_Restart_Binary(geometry[MESH_0], config, restart_filename);
1123  } else {
1124  Read_SU2_Restart_ASCII(geometry[MESH_0], config, restart_filename);
1125  }
1126 
1127  int counter = 0;
1128  long iPoint_Local = 0; unsigned long iPoint_Global = 0;
1129  unsigned long iPoint_Global_Local = 0;
1130  unsigned short rbuf_NotMatching = 0, sbuf_NotMatching = 0;
1131 
1132  /*--- Skip flow variables ---*/
1133 
1134  unsigned short skipVars = 0;
1135 
1136  if (nDim == 2) skipVars += 6;
1137  if (nDim == 3) skipVars += 8;
1138 
1139  /*--- Adjust the number of solution variables in the incompressible
1140  restart. We always carry a space in nVar for the energy equation in the
1141  mean flow solver, but we only write it to the restart if it is active.
1142  Therefore, we must reduce skipVars here if energy is inactive so that
1143  the turbulent variables are read correctly. ---*/
1144 
1145  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
1146  bool energy = config->GetEnergy_Equation();
1147  bool weakly_coupled_heat = config->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat();
1148 
1149  if (incompressible && ((!energy) && (!weakly_coupled_heat))) skipVars--;
1150 
1151  /*--- Load data from the restart into correct containers. ---*/
1152 
1153  counter = 0;
1154  for (iPoint_Global = 0; iPoint_Global < geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain(); iPoint_Global++ ) {
1155 
1156 
1157  /*--- Retrieve local index. If this node from the restart file lives
1158  on the current processor, we will load and instantiate the vars. ---*/
1159 
1160  iPoint_Local = geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_to_Local_Point(iPoint_Global);
1161 
1162  if (iPoint_Local > -1) {
1163 
1164  /*--- We need to store this point's data, so jump to the correct
1165  offset in the buffer of data from the restart file and load it. ---*/
1166 
1167  index = counter*Restart_Vars[1] + skipVars;
1168  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Solution[iVar] = Restart_Data[index+iVar];
1169  node[iPoint_Local]->SetSolution(Solution);
1170  iPoint_Global_Local++;
1171 
1172  /*--- Increment the overall counter for how many points have been loaded. ---*/
1173  counter++;
1174  }
1175 
1176  }
1177 
1178  /*--- Detect a wrong solution file ---*/
1179 
1180  if (iPoint_Global_Local < nPointDomain) { sbuf_NotMatching = 1; }
1181 
1182 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
1183  rbuf_NotMatching = sbuf_NotMatching;
1184 #else
1185  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&sbuf_NotMatching, &rbuf_NotMatching, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_SHORT, MPI_SUM, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1186 #endif
1187  if (rbuf_NotMatching != 0) {
1188  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The solution file ") + restart_filename + string(" doesn't match with the mesh file!\n") +
1189  string("It could be empty lines at the end of the file."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1190  }
1191 
1192  /*--- MPI solution and compute the eddy viscosity ---*/
1193 
1194 //TODO fix order of comunication the periodic should be first otherwise you have wrong values on the halo cell after restart.
1195  solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->Set_MPI_Solution(geometry[MESH_0], config);
1196  solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->Set_MPI_Solution(geometry[MESH_0], config);
1197 
1198  solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->Preprocessing(geometry[MESH_0], solver[MESH_0], config, MESH_0, NO_RK_ITER, RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS, false);
1199  solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->Postprocessing(geometry[MESH_0], solver[MESH_0], config, MESH_0);
1200 
1201  /*--- Interpolate the solution down to the coarse multigrid levels ---*/
1202 
1203  for (iMesh = 1; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
1204  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry[iMesh]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
1205  Area_Parent = geometry[iMesh]->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
1206  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Solution[iVar] = 0.0;
1207  for (iChildren = 0; iChildren < geometry[iMesh]->node[iPoint]->GetnChildren_CV(); iChildren++) {
1208  Point_Fine = geometry[iMesh]->node[iPoint]->GetChildren_CV(iChildren);
1209  Area_Children = geometry[iMesh-1]->node[Point_Fine]->GetVolume();
1210  Solution_Fine = solver[iMesh-1][TURB_SOL]->node[Point_Fine]->GetSolution();
1211  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1212  Solution[iVar] += Solution_Fine[iVar]*Area_Children/Area_Parent;
1213  }
1214  }
1215  solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->SetSolution(Solution);
1216  }
1217  solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->Set_MPI_Solution(geometry[iMesh], config);
1218  solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->Preprocessing(geometry[iMesh], solver[iMesh], config, iMesh, NO_RK_ITER, RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS, false);
1219  solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->Postprocessing(geometry[iMesh], solver[iMesh], config, iMesh);
1220  }
1221 
1222  /*--- Delete the class memory that is used to load the restart. ---*/
1223 
1224  if (Restart_Vars != NULL) delete [] Restart_Vars;
1225  if (Restart_Data != NULL) delete [] Restart_Data;
1226  Restart_Vars = NULL; Restart_Data = NULL;
1227 
1228 }

1467 void CTurbSASolver::Preprocessing(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh, unsigned short iRKStep, unsigned short RunTime_EqSystem, bool Output) {

1473  bool limiter_turb = ((config->GetKind_SlopeLimit_Turb() != NO_LIMITER) && (ExtIter <= config->GetLimiterIter()) && !(disc_adjoint && config->GetFrozen_Limiter_Disc()));

1508  Laminar_Viscosity = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();

1520 void CTurbSASolver::Postprocessing(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh) {
1521 
1522  su2double rho = 0.0, mu = 0.0, nu, *nu_hat, muT, Ji, Ji_3, fv1;
1523  su2double cv1_3 = 7.1*7.1*7.1;
1524  unsigned long iPoint;
1525 
1526  bool neg_spalart_allmaras = (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SA_NEG);
1527 
1528  /*--- Compute eddy viscosity ---*/
1529 
1530  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint ++) {
1531 
1532  rho = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
1533  mu = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
1534 
1535  nu = mu/rho;
1536  nu_hat = node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
1537 
1538  Ji = nu_hat[0]/nu;
1539  Ji_3 = Ji*Ji*Ji;
1540  fv1 = Ji_3/(Ji_3+cv1_3);
1541 
1542  muT = rho*fv1*nu_hat[0];
1543 
1544  if (neg_spalart_allmaras && (muT < 0.0)) muT = 0.0;
1545 
1546  node[iPoint]->SetmuT(muT);
1547 
1548  }

1552 void CTurbSASolver::Source_Residual(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *numerics, CNumerics *second_numerics,
1553  CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh) {
1554  unsigned long iPoint;
1555 
1556  bool harmonic_balance = (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == HARMONIC_BALANCE);
1557  bool transition = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() == LM);
1558  bool transition_BC = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() == BC);
1559 
1560  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
1561 
1562  /*--- Conservative variables w/o reconstruction ---*/
1563 
1564  numerics->SetPrimitive(solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive(), NULL);
1565 
1566  /*--- Gradient of the primitive and conservative variables ---*/
1567 
1568  numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), NULL);
1569 
1570  /*--- Set vorticity and strain rate magnitude ---*/
1571 
1572  numerics->SetVorticity(solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetVorticity(), NULL);
1573 
1574  numerics->SetStrainMag(solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetStrainMag(), 0.0);
1575 
1576  /*--- Set intermittency ---*/
1577 
1578  if (transition) {
1579  numerics->SetIntermittency(solver_container[TRANS_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetIntermittency());
1580  }
1581 
1582  /*--- Turbulent variables w/o reconstruction, and its gradient ---*/
1583 
1584  numerics->SetTurbVar(node[iPoint]->GetSolution(), NULL);
1585  numerics->SetTurbVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient(), NULL);
1586 
1587  /*--- Set volume ---*/
1588 
1589  numerics->SetVolume(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume());
1590 
1591  /*--- Get Hybrid RANS/LES Type and set the appropriate wall distance ---*/
1592 
1593  if (config->GetKind_HybridRANSLES() == NO_HYBRIDRANSLES) {
1594 
1595  /*--- Set distance to the surface ---*/
1596 
1597  numerics->SetDistance(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetWall_Distance(), 0.0);
1598 
1599  } else {
1600 
1601  /*--- Set DES length scale ---*/
1602 
1603  numerics->SetDistance(node[iPoint]->GetDES_LengthScale(), 0.0);
1604 
1605  }
1606 
1607  /*--- Compute the source term ---*/
1608 
1609  numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, NULL, config);
1610 
1611  /*--- Store the intermittency ---*/
1612 
1613  if (transition_BC) {
1614  node[iPoint]->SetGammaBC(numerics->GetGammaBC());
1615  }
1616 
1617  /*--- Subtract residual and the Jacobian ---*/
1618 
1619  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
1620 
1621  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
1622 
1623  }
1624 
1625  if (harmonic_balance) {
1626 
1627  su2double Volume, Source;
1628  unsigned short nVar_Turb = solver_container[TURB_SOL]->GetnVar();
1629 
1630  /*--- Loop over points ---*/
1631 
1632  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
1633 
1634  /*--- Get control volume ---*/
1635 
1636  Volume = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
1637 
1638  /*--- Access stored harmonic balance source term ---*/
1639 
1640  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nVar_Turb; iVar++) {
1641  Source = node[iPoint]->GetHarmonicBalance_Source(iVar);
1642  Residual[iVar] = Source*Volume;
1643  }
1644 
1645  /*--- Add Residual ---*/
1646 
1647  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
1648 
1649  }
1650  }
1651

2822

2825 
2826  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);

2829  conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel(), geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel());
2830

2832 
2833  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(tmp_residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
2834

2836 
2837  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
2838  Residual[iVar] += weight*tmp_residual[iVar];
2839 
2840  }
2841

2843 
2844  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
2845 
2846  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
2847 
2848  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
2849 
2850  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
2851  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
2852 
2853  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
2854 
2855  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(PrimVar_i, PrimVar_j);
2856  // visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
2857 
2858  /*--- Turbulent variables and its gradients ---*/
2859 
2860  visc_numerics->SetTurbVar(Solution_i, Solution_j);
2861  visc_numerics->SetTurbVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient());
2862 
2863  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
2864 
2865  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
2866 
2867  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
2868 
2869  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
2870 
2871  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
2872 
2873  }
2874  }
2875  }
2876  }
2877 
2878  /*--- Free locally allocated memory ---*/

2881  delete [] Normal;
2882  delete [] PrimVar_i;
2883  delete [] PrimVar_j;

3291  while (diff > tol) {
3292 
3293  func = nu_til_old*nu_til_old*nu_til_old*nu_til_old - (Eddy_Visc/Density_Normal)*(nu_til_old*nu_til_old*nu_til_old + Kin_Visc_Normal*Kin_Visc_Normal*Kin_Visc_Normal*cv1_3);
3294  func_prim = 4.0 * nu_til_old*nu_til_old*nu_til_old - 3.0*(Eddy_Visc/Density_Normal)*(nu_til_old*nu_til_old);
3295  nu_til = nu_til_old - func/func_prim;
3296 
3297  diff = fabs(nu_til-nu_til_old);
3298  nu_til_old = nu_til;
3299 
3300  counter++;
3301  if (counter > max_iter) {
3302  cout << "WARNING: Nu_tilde evaluation has not converged." << endl;
3303  break;
3304  }
3305 
3306  }
3307 
3308  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
3309  Solution[iVar] = nu_til;
3310 
3311  node[iPoint_Neighbor]->SetSolution_Old(Solution);
3312  LinSysRes.SetBlock_Zero(iPoint_Neighbor);
3313 
3314  /*--- includes 1 in the diagonal ---*/
3315 
3316  Jacobian.DeleteValsRowi(iPoint_Neighbor);
3317 
3318  }
3319 
3320  }
3321  }

3412  Deck

3450  case SA_EDDES:
3451

3453  Shur et al.

3460  vorticity[1]*vorticity[1] +
3461  vorticity[2]*vorticity[2]);

3473  delta[iDim] = fabs(coord_j[iDim] - coord_i[iDim]);

3856 void CTurbSSTSolver::Postprocessing(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh) {
3857  su2double rho = 0.0, mu = 0.0, dist, omega, kine, strMag, F2, muT, zeta;
3858  su2double a1 = constants[7];
3859  unsigned long iPoint;
3860 
3861  /*--- Compute mean flow and turbulence gradients ---*/
3862 
3863  if (config->GetKind_Gradient_Method() == GREEN_GAUSS) {
3864  SetSolution_Gradient_GG(geometry, config);
3865  }
3866  if (config->GetKind_Gradient_Method() == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES) {
3867  SetSolution_Gradient_LS(geometry, config);
3868  }
3869 
3870  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint ++) {
3871 
3872  /*--- Compute blending functions and cross diffusion ---*/
3873 
3874  rho = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
3875  mu = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
3876 
3877  dist = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetWall_Distance();
3878 
3879  strMag = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetStrainMag();
3880 
3881  node[iPoint]->SetBlendingFunc(mu, dist, rho);
3882 
3883  F2 = node[iPoint]->GetF2blending();
3884 
3885  /*--- Compute the eddy viscosity ---*/
3886 
3887  kine = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0);
3888  omega = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(1);
3889  zeta = min(1.0/omega, a1/(strMag*F2));
3890  muT = min(max(rho*kine*zeta,0.0),1.0);
3891  node[iPoint]->SetmuT(muT);
3892 
3893  }

3960 void CTurbSSTSolver::BC_Euler_Transpiration(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
3961  CNumerics *numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
3962 
3963  unsigned long iPoint, jPoint, iVertex, total_index, Point_Normal;
3964  unsigned short iDim, iVar;
3965  su2double distance, density = 0.0, laminar_viscosity = 0.0, beta_1;
3966 
3967  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
3968  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
3969 
3970  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
3971  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
3972 
3973  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
3974  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
3975 
3976  /*--- distance to closest neighbor ---*/
3977  jPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
3978  distance = 0.0;
3979  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
3980  distance += (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(iDim) - geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord(iDim))*
3981  (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(iDim) - geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord(iDim));
3982  }
3983  distance = sqrt(distance);
3984 
3985  /*--- Set wall values ---*/
3986  if (compressible) {
3987  density = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetDensity();
3988  laminar_viscosity = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
3989  }
3990  if (incompressible) {
3991  density = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetDensity();
3992  laminar_viscosity = solver_container[FLOW_SOL]->node[jPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
3993  }
3994 
3995  beta_1 = constants[4];
3996 
3997  Solution[0] = 0.0;
3998  Solution[1] = 60.0*laminar_viscosity/(density*beta_1*distance*distance);
3999 
4000  /*--- Set the solution values and zero the residual ---*/
4001  node[iPoint]->SetSolution_Old(Solution);
4002  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(Solution);
4003  LinSysRes.SetBlock_Zero(iPoint);
4004 
4005  /*--- Change rows of the Jacobian (includes 1 in the diagonal) ---*/
4006  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
4007  total_index = iPoint*nVar+iVar;
4008  Jacobian.DeleteValsRowi(total_index);
4009  }
4010 
4011  }
4012  }
4013
